	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Police
have launched a manhunt for armed men who fatally shot a 51-year-old man before
they robbed him of his firearm at Timane village in Dutywa in Eastern Cape,
police said on Tuesday. Captain Jackson Manatha said
Dutywa police were investigating murder and robbery cases following the fatal
shooting late on Monday. "The deceased was shot on
his upper body. The suspects then fled the scene with the firearm of the
deceased. No one has been arrested as yet," he said. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  